Studies in Texas and Louisiana marshes have demonstrated that production is related to temperature, salinity, and access to emergent marsh vegetation.  We are currently developing a systems model that will simulate recruitment, growth, and emigration of brown shrimp. This data will be used to help validate the model</dcterms:abstract>    <dc:publisher>Southeast Fisheries Science Center</dc:publisher>    <dc:creator>Leo, Jennifer </dc:creator>    <dc:creator>Galveston Laboratory</dc:creator>    <dc:identifier xsi:type="dcterms:URI">                 https://inport.nmfs.noaa.gov/inport/item/16990</dc:identifier>    <dcterms:isPartOf xsi:type="dcterms:URI">                 https://inport.nmfs.noaa.gov/inport/item/16983</dcterms:isPartOf>    <dcterms:spatial xsi:type="dcterms:Box">                         northlimit=29.493999;                         eastlimit=-94.845772;                         southlimit=29.181841;                         westlimit=-95.064125;                                              name=Four shallow marsh ponds.
